Hi,

I started out with the idea of making the test cases having the same package
as the classes under test, but I decided that this was messy, partly because
you have to work around anyway 
when accessing private fields/methods.

There is one basic solution:  Use the Java reflection API to access private
fields and methods.  Someone else mentioned JUnitX - I&#39;ve just had a brief
look at it, it looks like it uses this method to make it possible to do what
you ask.

Gabriel


&gt; when i write test case for application, normally i group all 
&gt; the testcases
&gt; in one package and application in another package. when i 
&gt; write test case
&gt; for applicaiton method, i encounter one problem:
&gt; some method is private, so testcase can not access it. i have 
&gt; to make the
&gt; method public.
&gt; in C++, we can use friend to solve this problem , but i can 
&gt; not do it in
&gt; java. 
&gt; any solution?
